[metadata]
Name=Black Vise Punisher
Description=Mono-artifact deck stuffed with Black Vise so random-vs-random play casts it early. On cast, Black Vise's ETB ChoosePlayer replacement picks the opponent (deterministic public-state pick: most cards in hand, then lowest PlayerId); at the beginning of the CHOSEN player's upkeep it deals max(0, handsize - 4) damage to that player (mtg-cuf0e). Used by the native-vs-WASM equivalence sweep to prove the ETB choose-player + the Count$ValidHand-4 upkeep damage replay BYTE-IDENTICALLY across compile targets. Mountains supply the {1} for the {1} Black Vise; Sol Ring / Mox Ruby accelerate. Mirror match guarantees both players cast Black Vise and choose each other.

[Main]
12 Mountain
8 Black Vise
4 Sol Ring
4 Mox Ruby
4 Ornithopter
4 Lightning Bolt
4 Shivan Dragon
